        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 16 at 6:37PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 637 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sterling, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sterling, Fleming and Reiradon Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
